{{Infobox person | name = Gérard Wertheimer | image = | birth_name = Gérard Paul Philippe Wertheimer | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|4|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Paris]], [[France]] | death_date = | death_place = | residence = [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]] | citizenship = [[Citizenship of the European Union|European]] | known_for = Co-Owner of [[Chanel|House of Chanel]] | net_worth = {{increase}} US$12.7 billion (November 2017)<ref name=ForbesBillionaires>[https://www.forbes.com/profile/gerard-wertheimer-1/ Forbes: Gérard Wertheimer] November 2017</ref> | spouse = Valérie Wertheimer | children = 3 | relations = {{Ubl|[[Alain Wertheimer]] (brother)|[[Pierre Wertheimer]] (grandfather)}} | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Paris]] | signature = }}
'''Gérard Paul Philippe Wertheimer''' (born April 17, 1951) is a [[France|French]] businessman based in [[Geneva]] who owns and controls the [[Chanel|House of Chanel]] [[perfume]] company in partnership with his brother, [[Alain Wertheimer|Alain]].<ref name=JPostRichestJews>[http://www.jpost.com/Home/Article.aspx?id=187421 Jerusalem Post: World's Richest Jews]</ref>
==Biography== Wertheimer was born to a [[French Jews|Jewish]] family,<ref name=JPostRichestJews /> the son of [[Jacques Wertheimer]] and Eliane Fischer. His grandfather, [[Pierre Wertheimer|Pierre]], co-founded the [[Chanel|House of Chanel]]. The privately held House of Chanel is run by Alain Wertheimer who has presided over the acquisition of several non-Chanel brands, including [[Eres Lingerie]], [[Tanner Krolle]] saddles and leather goods, and [[Holland & Holland]], a British gunsmith. Based in [[France]], the Wertheimer brothers own French vineyards including [[Château Rauzan-Ségla]] in [[Margaux]] and [[Château Canon (Saint-Émilion)|Château Canon]] in [[Saint-Emilion]], both of which have won rave reviews from oenophiles. Both brothers are enthusiastic [[Equestrianism|equestrian]]s who also inherited and operate an important [[thoroughbred]] [[horse racing]] stable they call [[La Presle Farm]] and/or Wertheimer farm for racing in the [[United States]] and in France as [[Wertheimer et Frère]] partnership.<ref>Didier Grumbach ''Histoires de la mode'' 2008 - Page 368 "Certaines autres sont de nature plus personnelle. Alain et Gérard Wertheimer ont hérité de leur grand-père, Pierre, grand amateur du Douanier Rousseau, sa passion pour l'art contemporain. Les chevaux de course étaient le péché mignon ... "</ref>
Gérard's wife Valérie is active in child protection charities.<ref>[[Paris Match]] Numéros 2971 à 2979 2006 - Page 101 "Epouse du richissime Gérard Wertheimer, Valérie Wertheimer aurait pu se contenter d'une existence légère et dorée. Mais, il y a six ans. traumatisée par la découverte des réseaux pédophiles via Internet, cette « boule d'énergie » a aussitôt ..."</ref>
