The '''Phosco P107''' was the [[lamp standard]] of choice for British [[council estate]]s in the 1960s.{{sfn|Middlefield|2017}}
It is a post top lantern with a single bulb.The lantern can run G.L.S. lamps up to 200.W, MB/U or MBF/U lamps up to 125W or 45-60W. sodium lamps.It is available with a large or small canopy. The [[Electrical ballast|ballast]] and the [[capacitor]] is kept in the actual column, It was first installed mainly around the City of Liverpool, then on housing estates throughout the United Kingdom. Low output columns were very suitable for the [[Radburn design housing|Radburn type layout]] popular on [[cottage estate]]s in the 1960s.
