[[File:Apsua Ladies in Flag Clothes.jpg|thumb|right|300x300px|Abkhaz women: One draped with the flag of the [[Republic of Abkhazia]], and the other clothed with a dress that was designed based on the flag.]]
{{Women in society sidebar}}
'''Abkhazian women''', particularly those of older age, are traditionally portrayed as [[peace maker|peacemaker]]s, [[decision maker]]s, and [[Mediation|mediator]]s in times of combat and conflict.  The women in Abkhazia only have a marginal in number within the showground of Abkhazian politics{{fact|date=October 2013}}.  At present, the Abkhazian females are more active as participants in the realm of business and in activities related to establishing organizations for women in their country.<ref name=IWPR>Gogoryan, Anaid. [http://iwpr.net/tk/node/50681 "Four women in parliament not an achievement, but a disgrace", says leading member], Abkhazia's Women Lament Under-Representation, Caucasus, CRS Issue 583, March 18, 2011, iwpr.net</ref><ref name=UNHCR>[http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/country,,,,GEO,,4d8c5a4d2,0.html Abkhazia’s Women Lament Under-Representation], Institute for War and Peace Reporting, March 18, 2011, unhcr.org (accessed on May 1, 2011)</ref>

